parameters: Oh, how beautiful... your body is...

I serve Lady Dorothea, the master of Blood Moon
Castle.
What the hell is going on?!
Do you really think you can defeat me?en(v[263]>=100)

To come this far and defy me with a blade...!
Unforgivable.
It's useless to run away! And... who are you?!

Oh, \v[111]-san... You haven't forgotten about
that incident, have you...?
Ugh... Of course... I haven't... forgotten...

Ugh... I have no choice... I'll pretend I didn't
see anything here... Hurry up and go somewhere
else...

\v[111], you came all over my body, didn't you?
Don't you want to do something pleasurable like
that again?
Ugh... Of course... I haven't... forgotten...

Ugh... I have no choice... I'll pretend I didn't
see anything here... Hurry up and go somewhere
else...

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

Well, you are... a face I haven't seen before.
Judging by your appearance, you must be one of
those magical girls from ReinGarnet that I've
heard about, right?

Nice to meet you. That's right, I'm Konoha.
Pleasure to meet you.

I am Dorothea, the mistress of this Blood Moon
Castle and the vampire who rules over this
territory. It's a pleasure to meet you as well.

This castle is amazing, isn't it? I'm sure it has
a rich history. It's surprising at first glance
because there doesn't seem to be a town.

Yes, that's right. You could say that this castle
is more of an illusion. The underground is
incredibly intricate, so its history is actually
longer over there.

By the way, I don't think you came here just for
sightseeing, did you? The fate of a magical
girl... there is only one thing...

Yes, of course. I'm traveling around various
regions to defeat demons for that purpose.

That's a good response. We, the LoliMon, have been
fighting against demons for a long time as well.
However, the stalemate has continued for thousands
of years now.

However, the fact that they are able to maintain
that state is because the demon's leader has not
yet been able to revive.

So, you're saying that the demons don't have a
true boss yet...? That's why they haven't fully
invaded... and

I see. However, recently the demons have been more
active. The army that you annihilated during your
reincarnation is part of that. In other words...

The revival of the demon boss, the demon god
Devil, is getting closer... or perhaps... there is
a fairly high possibility that it has already
awakened.

Our role as the Blood Moon is to build and observe
a watchtower in front of the fiery land, as the
Astalot Labyrinth is nearby, and we have been
doing so for many years.

What we are observing is... we are searching for a
way to cross that fiery land. Without finding a
way to cross those flames of hell, we cannot
launch an attack.

So we can't reach there unless we cross it. But
the demons are able to pass through... There must
be some secret.

Most likely, the biggest key is a large gate
called the Gate of Ten Thousand Demons that serves
as the entrance to the Fiery Land. I believe this
is the crucial point, but we have yet to obtain
confirmation.

I wonder if there's no other choice but to go
there directly, after all.

Currently, no magical girl who has passed through
that gate has returned. Don't rush and go there.
Especially strong magical girls like you.

Indeed, it would be a waste to go without any
information, right Dorothea? What should I do
first?

I see. I would like to immediately use the power
of my Lolimon... but unfortunately, I am currently
in a state of powerlessness.
You've lost your power? That's a big problem...

No, I generally understand the reasons, so that is
an issue that I should resolve. Therefore, there
is something I would like to ask of Konoha first.
Shall I leave it to you?

As I mentioned earlier, regarding the surveillance
tower... Recently, the regular communication has
been cut off, and I am concerned that something
may have happened.
It's a special place, after all. Who is there?

There are two surveillance officers, Kokori and
researcher Lolimon, and a magical girl named Rosia
who is in charge of communication. I wonder what
the reason is for Rosia not coming back...

Oh... that's dangerous. There's a possibility that
they might have been attacked. We need to hurry...

Rosia is quite a skilled magical girl, so it's
unlikely that something would happen within the
distance between this castle and the surveillance
tower. However, there is a possibility that
something is happening at the tower...
Alright, I'll go to the surveillance tower.

I would like you to go and check it out somehow.
There are no demons inside the tower, but there
are magical beasts for security. Please be
careful.

I will give you the key to the surveillance room
on the top floor of the surveillance tower. With
this, you can easily enter.

Nufu... What do you intend to do with me? You
can't do that.

The castle was devastated by the killing of
Dorothea of the Blood Moon. The castle and the
town were quickly taken over by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

Well, you are... a face I haven't seen before.
Judging by your appearance, you must be one of
those magical girls from ReinGarnet that I've
heard about, right?

Nufu... What do you plan to do to me? That won't
do.

The castle was devastated by the killing of
Dorothea of the Blood Moon. The castle and the
town were quickly taken over by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

I'm going. First, I'll hand over this observation
data.

Thank you for your hard work. I'll give you the
data later... So, was there something you needed?

The observer Kokori has become strange due to drug
addiction, and it seems that Rosia is away dealing
with that.

Oh my! Kokori, of all people... drug addiction,
you say? That's troublesome.

Maybe Rosia is moving to take measures for
treatment, but it seems like she's quite late.
Perhaps we should also start moving, don't you
think?

Perhaps something happened to Rosia while
exploring somewhere. Understood. There is someone
knowledgeable about detoxification methods for
addiction in our red-light district.

Please go to the tool shop in Pomlin. If you
explain the situation, I think they will
understand immediately and be able to create a
detoxification potion for us.

The underground red-light district, huh? I'll go
check it out. Once I've made the detoxification
potion, I'll head straight to the observation
tower.

Nice to meet you. There are stairs that lead down
to the red-light district from the 1st floor.

Nufu... What do you intend to do with me? That's
not acceptable.

The castle was devastated by the killing of
Dorothea of the Blood Moon. The castle and the
town were quickly taken over by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

It seems you've obtained the detox potion. Please
bring it to the surveillance tower quickly.

To reach the underground entertainment district,
there are stairs located on the southwest side of
the first floor of this castle. If you pass
through there, you will arrive.

Nufu... What do you intend to do to me? That won't
do.

The castle was devastated by the killing of
Dorothea of the Blood Moon. The castle and the
town were quickly taken over by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

Dorothea, I'm sorry. I got attacked by a demon at
the surveillance tower.

I heard the story. It seems that Konoha got
demonized and was attacked, so Rudia had no choice
but to run away. But I'm glad that both of them
are safe.

No, I am extremely incompetent... It is my
responsibility to protect that place. Lady
Dorothea, please punish me.

What are you saying? The problem isn't over yet.
There's no point in lamenting over what has
already passed.

Well, certainly, what should we do from now on?
But I wonder why Kokori suddenly turned into a
demon.

I suspected drug addiction, but it seems that it
was actually a precursor to demonization. It is
believed that the miasma pouring down on that
tower is the cause.

However, there should be a barrier for that... but
could it be that the barrier has weakened...?

That is highly possible. We should probably check
the barrier pillars once. However, I cannot leave
behind the researcher LoliMon who is still in the
tower.

I think they managed to escape well... But we also
need to confirm whether Kokori is still inside or
if she has come out of the tower.

Understood. Rosia, please return to the
surveillance tower and prioritize rescuing the
researchers. Let's have Konoha go and check the
barrier pillars.

The Ruins of the Crimson Bloodline has two
entrances, one in the north and one in the south.
Both connect underground and lead to the shrine.

The barrier pillars are quietly standing somewhere
in one of the underground chambers on the second
floor, either in the north or south. Please check
for any damage. There are a total of four pillars.

If they are damaged, you can tell the blacksmith
Lolonov in the downtown area, and he will
immediately go and repair them.

So there are a total of four pillars. After
confirming, we should go to the blacksmith in the
downtown area and request repairs. Understood.

Please take care of it. However, I don't think
this is the only thing, so I will also prepare the
next countermeasure.
What's wrong? Please calm down and tell me.

I see, so that's what happened... The barrier has
weakened to the point where demonization is
occurring...

Lady Dorothea! I'm sorry, I apologize for allowing
this situation to occur.

No, this is not Rosia's fault. The weakening of
the barrier is still my responsibility.

However...! It's possible that there is simply an
abnormality with the barrier pillars. Let's go
check the barrier pillars in the ruins.

I see. First and foremost, that is the priority.
However, Rosia, you must protect the surveillance
tower. If it falls into the hands of the demons,
we will be in serious trouble.

I'll leave it to Konoha. With her, there shouldn't
be any problems. Can you go, Konoha?

There are two entrances to the Crimson Bloodline
Ruins, one in the north and one in the south. Both
of them are connected underground, and either one
will lead you to the shrine.

The barrier pillars are quietly standing somewhere
in the underground second floor of either the
northern or southern antechamber, so please check
for any damage. There are a total of four of them.

If they are damaged, you can tell the blacksmith
Lolonov in the downtown area, and he will
immediately go to repair them.

So there are a total of four, right? After
confirming, we should go to the blacksmith in the
downtown area and request repairs. Understood.

Please take care of it. However, I don't think
this is the only issue, so I will also prepare the
next countermeasure.

Hehe... What do you plan to do with me? That won't
do.

The castle was devastated by killing Dorothea of
the Blood Moon. The castle and the town were
quickly dominated by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

The barrier pillars are quietly standing somewhere
in the basement of either the northern or southern
chamber on the second floor of the ruins, so
please check if there is any damage. There are a
total of four of them.

Nufu... What do you intend to do with me? That
won't do.

The castle was devastated by killing Dorothea of
the Blood Moon. The castle and the town were
quickly dominated by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

Dorothea, as expected, two of the barrier pillars
were indeed damaged. Just as we were told, I asked
the blacksmith to repair them for us.

As I expected. In that case, it means that the
barrier hasn't been restored yet...

I am measuring the current power of the barrier...
This is...
I wonder how it will turn out...

It seems that it hasn't fully returned. This is
indeed my own problem. With the current power
loss...

By the way, you mentioned that the power has been
lost. Is there any way to restore it somehow?

Yes, that's right. It involves performing a
certain ritual at the shrine... It needs to be
done once every 100 years, and we haven't finished
that ritual yet.

The ritual... If we do that, will the power be
restored...? If so, then the solution is simple.

Yes, that's true. However, that ritual is very
difficult, and when I did it for the first time, I
still had my parents who supported me. Thanks to
my mother and father, I was able to complete the
ritual.

I don't know what kind of ritual it is, but it
must be something significant. If we continue like
this, we will remain powerless and won't be able
to resist the demons, right?

Yes, that's right. It seems that the time has come
for us to make a decision.

The Crimson Bloodline ritual can be performed at
any time. It's up to Lady Dorothea to make the
decision.

I see... Understood. In that case, I will go to
the shrine, the shrine of the Crimson Bloodline.

It pains my heart, but I must ask Rosia for the
selection. I truly apologize for this. However, we
cannot continue like this.

Yes. Let's go. Since this is the case, Konoha-san,
I would like to ask you to accompany us, if
possible.

Yeah, that's right. If there's anything I can do
to help, I'll head to the shrine.

Dorothea-sama! It's urgent! Demons are causing a
commotion in front of the shrine! Please handle it
quickly!

What! In front of the shrine!? This is
unacceptable... Ah... It's my responsibility for
being so slow.

No way... Coco...? We have to finish her off this
time.
Let's hurry! We can't afford to lose this time...

Nufu... What do you intend to do with me? This
won't do.

town were quickly taken over by demons.

Oh! What a beautiful body you have. I can't let
myself be outdone either.

Konoha, the demons are very cunning. Be sure to be
careful...

Nufu... What do you intend to do to me? That won't
do.

The castle and the town were quickly taken over by
demons after the destruction of Dorothea, the
Blood Moon.

The castle was devastated by the killing of \C[3]
Dorothea of the Blood Moon. The castle and the
town were quickly taken over by demons.

Ah... Konoha... Why... why is this happening! Even
though she helped us so much.

So that's what happened. But now I think Devil-
sama's ideas are wonderful.

So that's what happened. But now I think Devil-
sama's ideas are wonderful.
It's a sad thing, but I have to defeat you...!

A magical girl who becomes an ally of the demons
is an enemy! It will never be forgiven.

The castle was devastated by killing Dorothea of
the Blood Moon. The castle and the town were
quickly dominated by demons.

Thanks to you, I have regained my power. If I had
been taken over by Sata at that time, this Blood
Moon Castle would have put an end to its history.

You did really well, Konoha. I appreciate your
efforts. Thank you.

It's fine. It's my duty to defeat the demons,
after all. The ritual was a success, but I won't
forget Rudia. To protect the town without
considering my own life, that's what a true
magical girl does, right?

Yes, indeed. You were truly admirable... Rudia
knew that I was avoiding this ritual.

But eventually, she must have been contemplating
about the ritual... In her own way.

Dorothea is just too kind. But well, I guess
that's why everyone follows her as their leader,
don't you think?

Well, now that my power has returned, I would like
to bestow a portion of my power to you as a
reward. Also, here is an item that appeared after
Sata's disappearance.

\C[2] Obtained the Crimson Moon Jewel and the
Sata's Emblem!
Thank you. I'll definitely be of use.

Yes, you who defeated the Four Heavenly Kings
might be able to cross that fiery demon zone...

That's right, in the end, we won't be able to
reach the demon's stronghold without crossing that
fiery demon zone.

Yes. Actually, new information has been revealed
from the observation data left by Kokori. This is
probably the secret of the Demon's Gate.

Good! With this, we can launch an attack on the
demon army!

It seems that there is a hidden path in the fiery
demon zone that is not normally visible. It
appears that there is a mechanism in the Demon's
Gate that allows it to become visible, but I don't
know what it is.

This is just my intuition, but the emblem I gave
you earlier... There is a high possibility that it
is related to the emblems held by the Four
Heavenly Kings.

In other words, if we can gather all of these
emblems... we might be able to break through.

Please proceed with caution at the Demon's Gate.
There are rumors of strong demons other than the
Four Heavenly Kings.
Alright, thank you. I'll do my best somehow.

Please be careful, as you may not have the
protection of the goddess Althea...

You really defeated the demon Four Heavenly Kings,
Sata. That's truly amazing. Thank you very much.

I was attacked when I infiltrated the Gate of Ten
Thousand Demons, so I had no choice but to defeat
them.

Thanks to your courageous actions, I have also
awakened. I have decided to finally perform the
important ritual that I have been avoiding.

Well then, I would like to bestow upon you a
portion of my power as a reward for your
achievements.
Thank you. I'll definitely be of use.

Yes. If you are the one who defeated all Four
Heavenly Kings and opened the Gate of Ten Thousand
Demons...

The path to the Astalot Labyrinth has been opened,
now all that's left is to go...
It will surely be a fierce battle, won't it...

Don't worry. We've made it this far, so we'll
manage somehow. Well then, see you later.

Please be careful, so that you may receive the
protection of the goddess Althea...

Thank you for that time, it was really scary,
wasn't it?

Thank you for that time, it was really scary,
wasn't it?

The surveillance tower is so scary... I wonder if
the barrier is okay...
